## 6. API Layer

### `GET /api/health`
Returns live system status. Checks presence of all 7 API keys.

```json
{
  "status": "OK | DEGRADED",
  "uptime": 123.4,
  "memory": {...},
  "api_keys": {
    "lastfm": true,
    "google": true,
    "mistral": false,
    ...
  },
  "missing_apis": ["mistral"]
}
```

Status is `DEGRADED` if any of the 4 required keys (lastfm, google, anthropic, openai) are missing.

---

### `GET /api/lastfm/:username?limit=10`
Fetches a user's recent Last.fm tracks.  
Returns an array of normalized track objects:
```json
{
  "username": "nightbeats",
  "tracks": [
    { "artist": "...", "title": "...", "album": "...", "playedAt": "...", "url": "...", "image": "..." }
  ],
  "count": 10
}
```

Additional endpoints:
- `GET /api/lastfm/artist/:artistName` — Returns bio, tags, listeners, playcount
- `GET /api/lastfm/track/:artistName/:trackName` — Returns duration, tags, wiki, playcount

---

### `POST /api/generate`
The main pipeline trigger.

**Request:**
```json
{ "artist": "Daft Punk", "title": "One More Time" }
```

**Response (success):**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "input": { "artist": "...", "title": "...", "mode": "artist_and_song" },
  "pipeline": {
    "stages": [
      { "stage": 1, "name": "analysis", "provider": "google", "processingTime": 1240, "success": true, "input": "...", "output": "..." },
      ...
    ],
    "totalProcessingTime": 18340,
    "stagesCompleted": 5,
    "errors": []
  },
  "result": {
    "prompt": "Energetic house track with filtered disco samples, four-on-floor beat, 123 BPM...",
    "characterCount": 198,
    "validation": { "valid": true, "errors": [], "warnings": [...], "suggestions": [...] }
  }
}
```

---

### `GET /api/generate/status`
Shows pipeline configuration and which providers are available/missing.

### `POST /api/generate/test-stage`
Allows isolated testing of any single pipeline stage (0–4) with arbitrary input. Useful for debugging.

