## 7. LLM Provider System

The `LLMProviderManager` implements a **class hierarchy** pattern:

```mermaid
classDiagram
    class LLMProvider {
        +name: string
        +config: object
        +makeRequest(prompt, options)*
        +isConfigured(): bool
    }

    class GoogleProvider {
        +model: gemini-1.5-flash
        +makeRequest()
    }
    class MistralProvider {
        +model: mistral-medium
        +makeRequest()
    }
    class DeepSeekProvider {
        +model: deepseek-chat
        +makeRequest()
    }
    class AnthropicProvider {
        +model: claude-3-haiku-20240307
        +makeRequest()
    }
    class OpenAIProvider {
        +model: gpt-4o-mini
        +makeRequest()
    }
    class PerplexityProvider {
        +model: llama-3.1-sonar-small-128k-online
        +makeRequest()
    }

    class LLMProviderManager {
        +providers: Map
        +getProvider(name)
        +getAvailableProviders()
        +getAllProviders()
        +makeRequest(name, prompt, options)
    }

    LLMProvider <|-- GoogleProvider
    LLMProvider <|-- MistralProvider
    LLMProvider <|-- DeepSeekProvider
    LLMProvider <|-- AnthropicProvider
    LLMProvider <|-- OpenAIProvider
    LLMProvider <|-- PerplexityProvider
    LLMProviderManager o-- GoogleProvider
    LLMProviderManager o-- MistralProvider
    LLMProviderManager o-- DeepSeekProvider
    LLMProviderManager o-- AnthropicProvider
    LLMProviderManager o-- OpenAIProvider
    LLMProviderManager o-- PerplexityProvider
```

> **Note:** `PerplexityProvider` is registered in the manager but **not used in any pipeline stage**. It is available for future use or direct API calls.

Each provider normalizes its response to a plain `string`, handling the different response shapes of each API (Google uses `.candidates[0].content.parts[0].text`, OpenAI/Mistral/DeepSeek use `.choices[0].message.content`, Anthropic uses `.content[0].text`).

All requests use a **60-second timeout** via axios.

---

## 8. Last.fm Integration

The `LastFmService` (`services/lastfm.js`) connects to the Last.fm REST API at `http://ws.audioscrobbler.com/2.0/`.

### Methods

| Method | Last.fm API Call | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `getUserRecentTracks(username, limit)` | `user.getrecenttracks` | Get listening history (up to 50) |
| `getArtistInfo(artistName)` | `artist.getinfo` | Bio, tags, listeners, playcount |
| `getTrackInfo(artistName, trackName)` | `track.getinfo` | Duration, tags, wiki, playcount |

### Normalization
- Filters out the "now playing" track (which has no timestamp)
- Handles Last.fm's inconsistent response shape (single track = object, multiple = array)
- Extracts the "large" image from the image array
- Converts Unix timestamps to `Date` objects

> `getArtistInfo` and `getTrackInfo` are **non-critical** — failures return `null` and are logged as warnings (not thrown), so a Last.fm metadata hiccup never blocks the main pipeline.

