## 9. Validation & Cleanup Engine

`PromptValidator` (`utils/prompt-validator.js`) enforces **Suno AI's content policy** on every generated prompt.

### Validation Checks (in order)

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A["Input: finalPrompt + artist + title"] --> B{"> 400 chars?"}
    B -->|Yes| ERR1["❌ error: length_exceeded"]
    B -->|No| C{Contains artist name?}
    C -->|Yes| ERR2["❌ error: artist_name_detected"]
    C -->|No| D{Contains song title?}
    D -->|Yes| ERR3["❌ error: song_title_detected"]
    D -->|No| E{Is English?}
    E -->|No| ERR4["❌ error: non_english_content"]
    E -->|Yes| F{Banned patterns?}
    F -->|Match| WARN1["⚠️ warning: suspicious_pattern"]
    F --> G{Required elements present?}
    G -->|Missing| WARN2["⚠️ warning: missing_elements\ngenre · tempo · instrument · mood"]
    G --> SUGG["💡 Generate suggestions"]
    SUGG --> OUT["Return ValidationResult"]
```

### Auto-Cleanup Sequence (in `routes/generate.js`)

If validation fails, the route automatically attempts repair **before returning an error**:

1. `cleanPrompt()` — strips artist/title word fragments using regex
2. `truncateIntelligently()` — cuts at sentence boundaries first, then word boundaries, appending `...`
3. `validatePrompt()` again — re-runs full validation on the cleaned version

### Required Elements Check

The validator checks for the presence of at least one term from each category:

| Element | Example keywords detected |
|---|---|
| **Genre** | rock, pop, jazz, electronic, hip-hop, house, techno, ambient, dubstep… |
| **Tempo** | BPM values, slow, fast, upbeat, downtempo, allegro, andante… |
| **Instrument** | guitar, piano, drums, bass, synthesizer, vocals, strings… |
| **Mood** | happy, energetic, dark, melancholic, dreamy, intense… |

Missing elements generate **warnings** (not errors) with improvement suggestions.

