## 10. Logging System

`Logger` (`utils/logger.js`) provides structured lifecycle logging.

### Log Events

| Event | Emoji | Method |
|---|---|---|
| Pipeline started | 🎵 | `logPipelineStart(artist, title)` |
| Stage starting | 🔄 | `logStageStart(num, name, provider)` |
| Stage succeeded | ✅ | `logStageSuccess(num, name, provider, output, ms)` |
| Stage errored | ❌ | `logStageError(num, name, provider, error)` |
| Fallback activated | 🔄 | `logFallbackUsed(num, primary, fallback)` |
| Pipeline finished | ✨ | `logPipelineComplete(totalMs, completed, chars)` |
| Validation result | 🔍 | `logValidationResult(valid, errors, warnings)` |
| HTTP request | 📡 | `logApiRequest(endpoint, method, status, ms)` |

### Output Modes

- **Console** — always active, with emoji-prefixed messages
- **File** (`./logs/pipeline.log`) — activated by `LOG_TO_FILE=true` in `.env`; auto-creates the `logs/` directory; format: `ISO_TIMESTAMP [LEVEL] message | Data: {...}`

