## Example End-to-End Output

**Input:**
```json
{ "artist": "Daft Punk", "title": "One More Time" }
```

**Stage 1 Output (Analysis):** ~800 words of musical analysis — filtered French house characteristics, Roland TR-909 drums, vocoder treatment, four-on-the-floor beat, disco sample manipulation, etc.

**Stage 2 Output (Refinement):**
```
GENRE & STYLE: French house, nu-disco, electronic dance
RHYTHM & TEMPO: 122-124 BPM, four-on-floor kick pattern...
INSTRUMENTATION: Filtered disco samples, Roland TR-909...
...
```

**Stage 3 Output (Enhancement):**
> *"A shimmering wall of filtered disco euphoria, four-on-floor kick punching through a warm analog haze..."*

**Stage 4 Output (Quality):** Trimmed, verified, professionally structured.

**Stage 5 Output (Final Prompt):**
> *"Energetic house track with filtered disco samples, four-on-floor beat, 123 BPM, vocoder vocals, funky bassline, uplifting chord progressions, electronic dance production"*

**Character count:** 176 / 400 ✅  
**Validation:** passed · no artist names · English only

